messages.body: Are you talking about python3-p2p module? Can't you just use pip3?
@piloth Oh... Are you talking about this? https://github.com/HelloZeroNet/Plugin-PeerMessage

piloth@zeroid.bit Oh and pip is a Python Package Installer. pip3 is the Python 3 version of it. I was pretty sleepy yesterday and honestly don't really know what you're talking about since I'm new here. But I wanted to test how this works and have a chat with someone.

piloth@zeroid.bit Ah, I see. Yeah, no problem I was looking to have a chat here. I've been starting to invest my time into 0Net since it reminds me so much of the internet of the past in several ways. By the way, they have tutorial for making zites with that plugin and it looks interesting.
And thanks for a fast response. I didn't think you or anyone would reply this fast.
I set up a ZeroNet on ThinkPad x60s for shits n' giggles and as of late I've been having way too much fun with this.
